The cell viability of TF-104 cultures treated with the two extracts and kuraridin was evaluated using the MTT assay (Fig. 3
). CC50 (50% cytotoxic concentration) values for the MeOH extract and EtOAc fraction were 253.3 and 278.4 μg/mL, respectively, while that for kuraridin was considerably lower at 302.2 μM (Table 1
). Accordingly, all experiments evaluating antiviral effects were performed at concentrations of minimal toxicity below 150 μg/mL for the MeOH extract and EtOAc fraction or 150 μM for kuraridin.
